$interpreted: Joan: "Step☆One──"
Joan: I'll disguise myself as the Storyteller and make sure the coast is clear!
Haunted House Employee: ...Huh? Ain't you our Storyteller?
Haunted House Employee: There's a private event this evening. We're not open now, so we won't be needin' ya for the moment. Too bad ye came all this way for nothin'!
Joan: What? I had no idea~~
Haunted House Employee: Well, we weren't too sure neither...
Joan: Since I'm here, just let me wait in the hall! I won't bother you one bit, I promise!
Haunted House Employee: ...Oh, well now...
Haunted House Assistant: It's the Storyteller! Of course we can let her in.
Joan: (This guy... He's the one who asked for my autograph earlier!)
Haunted House Employee: But ye said before—
Haunted House Assistant: Nevermind what I said! The Storyteller's a VIP. This is all our fault for not giving notice in advance.
Haunted House Assistant: Please, stay here as long as you wish. Right this way~
Joan: Right then, I'll make myself at home~~

Joan: "Step☆Two──"
Slip into the Boss's office unnoticed and nick that book!
Miranda: (What a strange collection—This must be the place. The boss is into some real weird stuff...)
Miranda: (—Waah!!!)
Miranda: (I can't even move my feet... Damn! This is so embarrassing—)
Miranda: ...Why am I the one who's got to steal the book?
Miranda: Isn't this a job for you and your super-stealthy cat-burgling ways?
Joan: Oh please, you're too kind~ You're not a puppet master like Tim, pulling all the strings behind the scenes. And we couldn't just leave you alone in the hall, either. So, here we are~~
Joan: You're a perfect little poltergeist, making mischief and moving things from their rightful place!!
Miranda: But...
Tindoiimu: Don't worry. We'll just think of something else if this doesn't work out.
Tindoiimu: After all, we're all in this together now.
Miranda: (I'm responsible to my new friends now, and I made a promise to that spirit... I can do this, I'm not alone—)
Miranda: (Yeah, now I think about it... I know I can do this!!)
Miranda: (...It's just like Joan said it would be. Awesome! Here it is!)
Miranda: (If I'm not wrong, the alarm should go off as soon as I grab the book. That's when we'll all regroup where we found Shirley—)
Miranda: Everything's going according to plan. We're all good!

Joan: "Step☆Three──"
Pretend to be contestants and storm the haunted house!
Tindoiimu: (The alarms are going off. I wonder if Miranda's managed to get hold of the book...)
Haunted House Employee: We're 'bout to lock the house down while we clarify the problem, all contestants please go to the main hall. We do apologize...
Tindoiimu: I left something valuable in here, I'll leave as soon as I've found it. Don't mind me.
Haunted House Employee: I... All right, but hurry yerself up!
Tindoiimu: (Now to lay low and wait for Miranda and Shirley. I'll disrupt the guards with these puppets Joan stole—)
Tindoiimu: (I'm not too familiar with them, but...)
Tindoiimu: You...
Fog Sect Soldier: —You! Wait, you're... Princess Tindoiimu?
Tindoiimu: Uh... Is something the matter?
Fog Sect Soldier: Ah...
Fog Sect Soldier: We've received a tip-off that there's a thief in the haunted house tonight... We've been lying in wait to ambush her here!
Tindoiimu: (Oh no! No wonder they weren't open to regular guests tonight... I better hurry and tell the others to call it off!)
Fog Sect Soldier: Not to worry! We've already set our trap. We won't let her or a single one of her accomplices get away!
Tindoiimu: Accomplices?
Fog Sect Soldier: Yup, there's more than one of 'em... We don't know who they are, but we'll be sure to find out once we get to the interrogation!
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: (If we don't call it off now, then it looks like even I'll be found out eventually—)
Fog Sect Soldier: I'll have one of the men escort you to safety.
Fog Sect Soldier: Princess?
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: Okay.
Miranda: Shirley? What's all this mess! What happened here!?
Shirley: Don't cry... M-my baby...
Miranda: Have you lost your mind?
Miranda: Don't worry, I'm here to get you out of here!
Shirley: —No! G-get out... You're in danger... It's already too late...
Miranda: ...What?
Shirley: Just like that day, with the storm, and the crying... Z-Zola—
Shirley: Eh? Who... Who's she...
Miranda: Joan hasn't signalled any danger. It's all quiet outside... So we ought to continue with our plan...
Miranda: —I'm gonna rescue you!!
Miranda: It's all blank inside!? What the—
Haunted House Boss: That's because I've seen right through your dastardly plans~
Haunted House Boss: Crazy, right? I bet you're wondering who sold you out. I've planned this whole thing, just so I could catch the lot of you~
Haunted House Boss: After all... when you control the spirits, you control their secrets too! I've kept an eye on Shirley's every move, just as it appears in the real book~
Miranda: Enslaved, imprisoned, and humiliated... You're simply despicable.
Haunted House Boss: Hmph! You're small fry to somebody like me! Anyway, you won't be shooting your mouth off for much longer.
Miranda: Try me.
Haunted House Boss: Me? Oh no, I'm far too precious to dirty my hands with the likes of you.
Haunted House Boss: Of course, with all those tricks of yours, I expect you'd easily outfox any regular guard, so...
Haunted House Boss: —Shirley.
Miranda: Shirley...!
Shirley: Wah, I...
Shirley: Haaagh!
Haunted House Boss: You dare disobey—
Miranda: Behold!
Miranda: ......
Shirley: Must... protect...
Miranda: ...I won't hurt you.
Haunted House Boss: Time to knock this jumped-up brat down a peg or two!
Miranda: But you, I'll fight to the very end. So... Watch it!
